E. Acquisition Strategy
Milestone C decision for LRIP was held June 24, 2011. The Block II program received USN Initial Operational Capability (IOC) in March 2015 and FRP Approval in
August 2015. The Air Force achieved IOC in September 2016. In February 2019, the Acquisition Program Baseline (APB) for SAF was revised to increase total missile
procurements and extend missile procurements through 2035. The program awarded FRP-8 in March 2022, and FRP-9 awarded in December 2022.

 Counter Unmanned Aircraft Systems Development:
 Development effort for cost effective Counter-Unmanned Aircraft System (c-UAS) solution by maturing air-to-air design to TRL 6/7 to counter growing UAS threat.


