Title: Radar Landing System (RLS) Mod Kit Development                                                                 0.000       0.000      14.272      0.000      14.272
                                                                                                      Articles:          -           -           -          -           -
Description: In accordance with the CNO approved 2022 PALC Roadmap update, AN/SPN-35, AN/SPN-41,
and AN/SPN-46 systems were planned to sundown upon fielding of the AN/SPN-51 Brizo Landing System. To
ensure Precision Approach Landing Capabilities were maintained on CVN and LHA/LHD class ships through
AN/SPN-51 fielding, continued subsystem development efforts were planned to address emerging system
issues within legacy Radar Landing Systems (RLS) and design / test of system modification kits. With the
2025 cancellation of the AN/SPN-51 efforts, a thorough assessment of system obsolescence issues, remaining
component service life, and component manufacturing capabilities are required. These preliminary efforts
support the definition and development of future AN/SPN-35, AN/SPN-41, and AN/SPN-46 mod kits. RLS mod
kit design work will require procurement and testing to ensure modifications provide obsolescence mitigations
critical to extending system life to 2040.

FY 2025 Plans:
N/A
FY 2026 Base Plans:
Design/development of AN/SPN-41 system modifications to implement modified circuit card assemblies (CCAs)
and Field-Programmable Gate-Arrays (FPGAs) that replace legacy hardware that is no longer commercially
available and that support future SW upgrades required to maintain cyber resiliency. Includes development
material procurements and preliminary contractor testing of subsystem modification kits. Legacy system
obsolescence and service life assessments will be conducted that review existing system reliability, parts
availability and manufacturing sources to inform prioritization of system modifications. Initial design and

