A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
Organic Precision Fires (OPF) is a Marine Corps modernization priority and will provide multiple echelons of the Fleet Marine Force with an organic, loitering, beyond-
line-of-sight precision strike capability. OPF will deliver precision effects as well as surveillance before and during target strike, while reducing the potential for collateral
damage. Multiple materiel solutions are required to provide the envisioned capabilities to the Fleet Marine Force.

OPF-Light will procure an existing, light-weight loitering munition for use by dismounted elements. It provides a dismounted, lightweight, man-packable, loitering munition
that extends the capability of the infantry squad/platoon to engage targets to the maximum range of organic Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (ISR) assets
at that level. OPF-Light will provide a counter-defilade, anti-personnel and anti-materiel capability. Primary target sets for this system will be enemy personnel, crew-
served weapons, and Command and Control (C2) nodes. This will be principally a platoon/squad level asset.

In FY 2025, the program completed Developmental Testing 1 (DT1) and initiated Developmental Testing 2 (DT2). In FY 2026, OPF-Light will complete DT2, conduct
operational testing, and begin development and testing of OPF capability enhancements. OPF capability enhancements will provide greater lethality effects over the
base capability including upgrades for target recognition and warhead performance.

