-Continue Passive Acoustic Monitoring research efforts on passive acoustics and other technology supporting
wide area surveillance, including the development and testing of new autonomous hardware platforms and
signal processing algorithms for detection, classification, and localization of marine species.

-Continue research to advance our understanding of sound reception mechanisms in large whales including
the anatomy surrounding the ear and the whole head to improve and validate finite element models of sound
propagation through various tissues.

-Continue research using animal tagging and passive acoustic monitoring to quantify behaviors, movement, and
distribution of marine species relative to key environmental properties and sonar exposure, both incidental and
experimental.

-Continue Sonar Exposure research to quantify the behavioral and physiological effects to potentially population-
level consequences of sonar exposure on marine life to develop risk criteria for Navy's sound effects modeling,

