ONR's research in areas like the "Fleet Tactical Grid" aims to ensure that every warfighter has access to the
information they need to make critical decisions. This requires a robust internal and external communications
network to support the development and testing of these advanced systems.

- Continue Facilities and Infrastructure: ONR's headquarters in Arlington, Virginia, and its global offices require
ongoing maintenance and support to provide a secure and efficient work environment.

- Continue Information Technology (IT) Support: The complex and data-intensive nature of ONR's work demands
a high-performance IT infrastructure with robust cybersecurity protections. This includes everything from data
storage and processing to software licensing and technical support.
