A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This Program Element (PE) provides funding for the essential corporate expenses that form the foundational support structure for the Office of Naval Research (ONR).
These costs, the vast majority of which are fixed, include salaries for the world-class scientists and engineers who lead our S&T programs, as well as critical operational
expenses such as Information Technology (IT), cyber security efforts, Defense Finance and Accounting Service (DFAS) billings, and day-to-day logistical support. This
investment is not merely overhead but a direct enabler of ONR's core mission to discover, develop, and transition innovative science and technology. This foundational
support ensures that ONR can continue to provide the U.S. Navy and Marine Corps with the decisive technological advantage required to preserve national security.

