A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This Project provides funds for non-Labor costs associated with executing ONR's mission to discover, develop, and transition innovative science and technology (S&T)
to meet current and future needs of naval forces. Majority of funds in this project are fixed costs, such as communications, training, and other support functions.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                             FY 2027 FY 2027 FY 2027
                                                                                                                        FY 2025 FY 2026          Base    OOC     Total
Title: Science and Technology Management                                                                                   5.131   5.370           5.354   0.000   5.354
Description: This Project provides funding for the essential non-labor costs that form the foundational support
structure for the Office of Naval Research (ONR) to execute its mission of discovering, developing, and
transitioning innovative science and technology (S&T) to naval forces. While categorized as non-labor, these are
primarily fixed costs crucial for mission success, directly enabling vital functions such as global communications
for international collaboration, continuous training to keep our scientific workforce at the cutting edge, and other
critical support like IT infrastructure and program management. This investment is not merely overhead but
a direct enabler of the research and development enterprise that ensures the U.S. Navy and Marine Corps
maintain their decisive technological advantage, ultimately preserving national security.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue education of world-class workforce. ONR employs top, world-class scientists and engineers.
To maintain this level of expertise, ongoing training in the latest scientific methodologies, technological
advancements, and project management techniques is essential.

- Continue Global Collaborations. Global presence allows ONR to identify and foster groundbreaking research
from international partners. Effective communication systems are the lifeblood of this international collaboration,
enabling real-time data sharing, video conferencing, and secure correspondence with researchers and
institutions worldwide.

- Continue Information Dissemination: ONR is responsible for disseminating research findings, funding
opportunities, and technological updates to a vast network of stakeholders, including the Naval Research and
Development Establishment (NRDE), academic partners, and industry. This requires a sophisticated and reliable
communications infrastructure to manage everything from broad agency announcements to secure data transfer.

