Title: Weapons Technology                                                                                                 0.000       0.000      12.000      0.000       12.000
                                                                                                          Articles:          -           -           -          -            -
Description: This activity advances Navy strategic goals by maturing kinetic weapon system and sub-system
science and technologies to greatly enhance performance and novel capabilities for current and future offensive
and defensive kinetic weapons at a reasonable cost that will overmatch adversarial platforms and capabilities.
Successful development will enable weapons with enhanced range, speed, lethality, and payload capacity within
stringent Size, Weight, Power, and Cost (SWaP-C) and platform constraints. Science and Technology efforts will
encompass tactical propulsion and weapon airframes, improved payloads, enablers for Find Fix Target Track
(F2T2) capabilities, and collaborative weapon networking and weapon autonomy.
Efforts will extend to include ancillary systems, materials development, and cost reduction activities, culminating
in a high-TRL demonstrations of integrated, longer-range and more lethal weapon systems. Specific activities
of coordinated RDT&E projects include: advanced weapon-specific materials and manufacturing development;
cost reduction activities for novel propulsion components and electronic support systems; battery reliability
and production risk mitigation; flight control and aerodynamic performance optimization; fuel system and
kinetic energy management; advanced payload, fuzing, and target detection design; affordable and mass-
manufacturable boost motor design, collaborative weapons, and weapon autonomy. The investment supports
Department of War (DoW) priorities for affordable mass munitions and accelerates combat technologies. This
effort leverages prior applied research and is not a new start.

