A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This Program Element supports Department of War (DoW) priorities for enduring science and technology (S&T) for nuclear re-entry systems. For several decades,
foundational nuclear R&D investments outside of major acquisition programs have been significantly reduced. This historical trend contrasts with the DoW's recent
recognition of the need to invest in advanced nuclear-related components and technologies in support of the nuclear enterprise, nuclear deterrence operations, and
integrated deterrence operations. This effort will provide pre-program of record advanced technology development that will effectively address evolving threats and
maintain operational effectiveness while also aligning with the highest-level guidance for nuclear forces identified in the Nuclear Posture Review and National Defense
Strategy. This effort will contribute to preserving the viability of the nuclear deterrent in a cost-effective manner by reducing technical and programmatic risk associated
with execution of the overall nuclear modernization program. These ends will be reached by developing technologies to inform future system requirements, establishing
interagency partnerships for re-entry system test platform development, and coordinating with existing programs for next generation strategic system development.

 In conjunction with U.S. Strategic Command (STRATCOM) Priorities and collaboration with Air Force, the Nuclear Delivery Systems (NDS) funding will identify and
 mature technologies from Technology Readiness Level (TRL) 3 to TRL 6 via relevant ground and flight test environments.

